This paper deals with auction theory and mechanism design, which are central topics in game theory and economics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). The paper also discusses revenue optimization, which is a common goal in auctions, and thus it could also belong to cs.EC (Economics and Computation). The paper uses mathematical proofs and analysis, indicating that it could also fit into cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the role of discrimination and simultaneity in auctions, which could make it relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well.
